                    "creation_date": 1411659285,
                    "answer_id": 26042516,
                    "question_id": 26042390,
                    "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/26042390/git-add-asterisk-vs-git-add-period/26042516#26042516",
                    "body": "<p><code>*</code> is not part of git - it's a wildcard interpreted by the shell. <code>*</code> expands to all the files in the current directory, and is only then passed to git, which <code>add</code>s them all.\n<code>.</code> is the current directory itself, and <code>git add</code>ing it will add it and the all the files under it.</p>\n"
