                            "comment_id": 95025146,
                            "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/26042390/git-add-asterisk-vs-git-add-period/26042555#comment95025146_26042555",
                            "body": "@Thor84no: Git will find the dot-files even on a Linux system, if you quote the <code>*</code> to protect it from the shell. It&#39;s not a matter of the hidden bit, it&#39;s just that Git&#39;s compiled-in rules differ."
