                            "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/26042390/git-add-asterisk-vs-git-add-period/49328932#comment95222654_49328932",
                            "body": "Thank you @reka18, for a very good question. It inspired me to complete my answer...  The answer to your question: If you call it in the working directory, no, but if in a subdirectory, then yes (<code>git add -A</code> applies to the entire working directory and <code>git add .</code> always the current directory)."
